{
  "text": "Some studies have shown that cholecystectomy is useful in patients with biliary-like pain when the GBEF is reduced. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] In contrast, 1 meta-analysis did not indicate a value of GBEF for predicting outcome after cholecystectomy in patients with recurrent abdominal pain suggestive of biliary disease without abnormal findings by conventional diagnostic tests. [CITATION_3] We could not analyze symptom improvement after cholecystectomy in patients with atypical biliary pain and reduced GBEF because of insufficient medical records.",
